			<description><![CDATA[<p>
	Part of our mission is to hire the best talent in support of being the employer of choice.&nbsp; Our goal is to be&nbsp;number one&nbsp;at providing a world class customer experience so we are looking for the best employees and talent to join our team and enjoy the ride to the top.</p>
<p>
	Summary:<br />
	As a Workforce Analyst at Spark Networks (www.spark.net), you will be responsible for forecasting calls and all other customer service tasks, scheduling customer service agents appropriately so as to ensure service and utilization levels are efficiently met, and reporting on call center performance daily, weekly, and monthly. You will also be responsible for identifying in real time changes in call volume and adjusting staffing accordingly.</p>
<p>
	This position requires someone who is highly organized, has excellent communication and follow-through, and can use good-judgment.&nbsp; Highly motivated individuals who are passionate about quality, world-class service, and are highly detail oriented are encouraged to apply.</p>
<p>
	Job duties:</p>
<ul>
	<li>
		Ensure attainment of key WFM metrics, including service level, occupancy, utilization, forecast accuracy, schedule efficiency and adherence</li>
	<li>
		Develop shift schedules and manage time off requests to ensure optimal staffing.</li>
	<li>
		Proactively gather and schedule offline requests and priorities from management.</li>
	<li>
		Promote overtime and voluntary time off as necessary to close interval-level staffing gaps</li>
	<li>
		Create schedules for new hires</li>
	<li>
		Administer shift bid process and realign schedules as necessary</li>
	<li>
		Reporting of hourly, daily, weekly, monthly stats for sales, KPIs and other WFM metrics</li>
	<li>
		Deliver a detailed post mortem analysis for days/times when Service Level was not met for prior day(s).</li>
	<li>
		Recommend real-time schedule changes and identify efficiency opportunities. Collaborate with the Customer Support leadership team to develop and leverage best practices to reach shared goals</li>
	<li>
		Make recommendations to maximize resources and meet customer expectations.</li>
</ul>
<p>
	Requirements:</p>
<ul>
	<li>
		2+ years experience in Workforce Management planning and scheduling</li>
	<li>
		Strong knowledge of Workforce Management theory and best practices</li>
	<li>
		4 year college degree preferred</li>
	<li>
		Demonstrated ability to use sound judgment and fairness when administering policies and procedures.</li>
	<li>
		Demonstrates exceptional critical thinking and analytical skills.</li>
	<li>
		Must have expert proficiency in Microsoft Office software, particularly Excel.</li>
	<li>
		Must possess excellent written and verbal communication skills</li>
	<li>
		High attention to detail.</li>
</ul>
